definitions.definition: An insect of the order Coleoptera referring to certain species of rove beetles , particularly in the genus Paederus. Known for secreting a potent irritant , pederin, which can cause severe skin irritation and blistering when contacted.

secondary_definitions: ( Southeast Asia ) An insect of the order Coleoptera referring to certain species of rove beetles , particularly in the genus Paederus. Known for secreting a potent irritant , pederin, which can cause severe skin irritation and blistering when contacted.
